about.summary: Extensions to 'ggplot2' respecting the grammar of graphics paradigm. Specialization of method ggplot(): accept and convert on the fly time series data. Geom: "table", "plot" and "grob" add insets to plots using native data coordinates, while "table_npc", "plot_npc" and "grob_npc" do the same using "npc" coordinates through new aesthetics "npcx" and "npcy". Statistics: locate and tag peaks and valleys; count observations in different quadrants of a plot; select observations based on 2D density; label with the equation of a polynomial fitted with lm() or other types of models; labels with P-value, R^2 or adjusted R^2 or information criteria for fitted models; label with ANOVA table for fitted models; label with summary for fitted models. Model fit classes for which suitable methods are provided by package 'broom' are supported. Scales and stats to build volcano and quadrant plots based on outcomes, fold changes, p-values and false discovery rates.

name: r-ggpmisc
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "0.4.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggpmisc
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggpmisc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggpmisc/ggpmisc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 33fecbecefedb7e5260662d4cde58ba2d8f484a1e3d90276608818229727c839

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass >=7.3_51.6
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.2
    - r-generics >=0.1.0
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.3.1
    - r-ggpp >=0.4.2
    - r-lmodel2 >=1.7_3
    - r-lubridate >=1.7.9
    - r-plyr >=1.8.6
    - r-polynom >=1.4_0
    - r-quantreg >=5.85
    - r-rlang >=0.4.7
    - r-scales >=1.1.1
    - r-splus2r >=1.2_2
    - r-tibble >=3.0.3
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass >=7.3_51.6
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.2
    - r-generics >=0.1.0
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.3.1
    - r-ggpp >=0.4.2
    - r-lmodel2 >=1.7_3
    - r-lubridate >=1.7.9
    - r-plyr >=1.8.6
    - r-polynom >=1.4_0
    - r-quantreg >=5.85
    - r-rlang >=0.4.7
    - r-scales >=1.1.1
    - r-splus2r >=1.2_2
    - r-tibble >=3.0.3

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggpmisc')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggpmisc')\""  # [win]

Geom: \"table\", \"plot\" and \"grob\" add insets to plots using native data coordinates, while \"table_npc\", \"plot_npc\" and \"grob_npc\" do the same using\
    \ \"npc\" coordinates through new aesthetics \"npcx\" and \"npcy\".     \ adjusted R^2 or information criteria for fitted models; label with ANOVA table for fitted models; label with summary for fitted models. Model fit classes for which suitable methods are provided by package 'broom' are supported. Scales and stats to build volcano and quadrant plots based on outcomes, fold changes, p-values\

  license_family: GPL2

    - conda-forge/r
